<subSubSection id="C30D6531FFDEFF92FF40F93FFEFEF8AF" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="173" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA836BAFFDEFF92FF40F93FFEFEF8AF" blockId="18.[151,1436,1604,2025]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1437,1613,1962]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="173" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDEFF96FF40F93FFEE5F968" bold="true" box="[199,315,1676,1701]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDEFF96FEC2F93FFDC2F969" authorityName="A. Carausu" authorityYear="1941" box="[325,540,1676,1701]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDEFF96FEC2F93FFDC2F969" box="[325,540,1676,1701]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Parvipalpus major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDEFF96FD7FF93FFC77F969" author="Carausu, A." box="[760,937,1676,1700]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref18749" refString="Carausu, A. (1941) Note sur quelques Caprellides des eaux francaises et monegasques. Bulletin de l'lnstitut oceanographique, Monaco, 38, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">Carausu (1941)</bibRefCitation>
based on material from the Mediterranean coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F300762AFFDEFF96FF70F903FE9DF90A" box="[247,323,1712,1735]" name="France" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">France</collectingCountry>
(Banyuls-sur-Mer) and 
<collectingCountry id="F300762AFFDEFF96FDD2F903FD6DF90A" box="[597,691,1712,1735]" name="Monaco" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Monaco</collectingCountry>
, and was considered as Mediterranean endemic by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDEFF96FB7EF91CFF3BF921" author="Krapp-Schickel, T." pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="773 - 809" refId="ref21001" refString="Krapp-Schickel, T. (1993) Suborder Caprellidea. In: Ruffo, S. (Ed.), The Amphipoda. of the Mediterranean. Memoires de l'Institut oceanographique de Monaco, 13, 773 - 809." type="journal article" year="1993">Krapp-Shickel (1993)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDEFF96FF75F967FDDBF920" author="Laubitz, D. R. &amp; Sorbe, J. C." box="[242,517,1748,1773]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="626 - 632" refId="ref21383" refString="Laubitz, D. R. &amp; Sorbe, J. C. (1996) Deep-water caprellids (Amphipoda: Caprellidea) from the Bay of Biscay: a new species and a new locality record. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 16, 626 - 632. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1548754" type="journal article" year="1996">Laubitz &amp; Sorbe (1996)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the species based on material from North Atlantic (Bay of Biscay). The Mediterranean specimens of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDEFF96FD89F94BFD65F8DD" author="Carausu, A." box="[526,699,1784,1808]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref18749" refString="Carausu, A. (1941) Note sur quelques Caprellides des eaux francaises et monegasques. Bulletin de l'lnstitut oceanographique, Monaco, 38, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">Carausu (1941)</bibRefCitation>
were found from 
<quantity id="4CEF9B5FFFDEFF96FC01F944FBCAF8C2" box="[902,1044,1783,1808]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5025" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.005" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" unit="m" value="150.25" valueMax="300.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5 to 300 m</quantity>
depth, and the Atlantic material of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDEFF96FF10F8AFFE7DF8F8" author="Laubitz, D. R. &amp; Sorbe, J. C." box="[151,419,1820,1845]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="626 - 632" refId="ref21383" refString="Laubitz, D. R. &amp; Sorbe, J. C. (1996) Deep-water caprellids (Amphipoda: Caprellidea) from the Bay of Biscay: a new species and a new locality record. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 16, 626 - 632. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1548754" type="journal article" year="1996">Laubitz &amp; Sorbe (1996)</bibRefCitation>
were collected from 
<quantity id="4CEF9B5FFFDEFF96FD15F8AFFCCBF8F9" box="[658,789,1820,1845]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.495" metricValueMax="9.24" metricValueMin="1.75" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" unit="m" value="549.5" valueMax="924.0" valueMin="175.0">
175– 
<specimenCount id="9D11FD33FFDEFF96FD4EF8AFFCCBF8F9" box="[713,789,1820,1845]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" type="generic">924 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDEFF96FCA7F8AFFBD8F8F8" author="Corbari, L. &amp; Sorbe, J. C. &amp; Massabuau, J. C." box="[800,1030,1820,1845]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="363 - 371" refId="ref18881" refString="Corbari, L., Sorbe, J. C. &amp; Massabuau, J. C. (2005) Video study of the caprellid amphipod Parvipalpus major: morphofunctional and behavioural adaptations to deep-sea bottoms. Marine Biology, 146, 363 - 371. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00227 - 004 - 1433 - 4" type="journal article" year="2005">
Corbari 
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDEFF96FCFBF8AEFC6BF8F8" box="[892,949,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">et al.</emphasis>
(2005)
</bibRefCitation>
conducted a detailed video study of this species where they showed morpho-functional and behavioural adaptations to deep-sea bottoms. Our male specimens show the same morphology than that described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDEFF96FCCDF8D7FB88F8B0" author="Laubitz, D. R. &amp; Sorbe, J. C." box="[842,1110,1892,1917]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="626 - 632" refId="ref21383" refString="Laubitz, D. R. &amp; Sorbe, J. C. (1996) Deep-water caprellids (Amphipoda: Caprellidea) from the Bay of Biscay: a new species and a new locality record. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 16, 626 - 632. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1548754" type="journal article" year="1996">Laubitz &amp; Sorbe (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and females are also in good agreement with the original figures and description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDEFF96FC95F83BFC18F86D" author="Carausu, A." box="[786,966,1928,1952]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref18749" refString="Carausu, A. (1941) Note sur quelques Caprellides des eaux francaises et monegasques. Bulletin de l'lnstitut oceanographique, Monaco, 38, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">Carausu (1941)</bibRefCitation>
; the dorsal surface of male pereonites is smooth while it is full of tiny tubercles in females. Although morphological evidences seem to demonstrate that the species inhabits both Atlantic and Mediterranean waters, further molecular studies could aid to explore if Mediterranean and Atlantic populations belong to the same species, or if, otherwise, there is enough genetic differentiation to consider them to belong to different cryptic species. So far, the genus comprises 5 described species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FF7DF925FDAEF963" authority="(Chevreux, 1888)" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1888" baseAuthorityName="Chevreux" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[250,624,1685,1710]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capillaceus">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FF7DF925FE47F963" box="[250,409,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. capillaceus</emphasis>
(Chevreux, 1888)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FDF8F925FCA9F963" authority="Mayer, 1890" authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1890" box="[639,887,1685,1710]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linea">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FDF8F925FD09F963" box="[639,727,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. linea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDAFF92FD65F925FCA9F963" author="Mayer, P." box="[738,887,1686,1710]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" pagination="1 - 157" refId="ref21638" refString="Mayer, P. (1890) Die Caprelliden des Golfes von Neapel und der angrenzenden Meeres-Abschnitte. Nachtrag zur Monographie derselben. Fauna und Flora des Golfes von Neapel, 17, 1 - 157. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 53624" type="journal article" year="1890">Mayer, 1890</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FC01F925FB45F963" authority="Carausu, 1941" authorityName="A. Carausu" authorityYear="1941" box="[902,1179,1686,1710]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FC01F925FC36F960" box="[902,1000,1686,1709]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. major</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDAFF92FC74F925FB45F963" author="Carausu, A." box="[1011,1179,1686,1710]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref18749" refString="Carausu, A. (1941) Note sur quelques Caprellides des eaux francaises et monegasques. Bulletin de l'lnstitut oceanographique, Monaco, 38, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">Carausu, 1941</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FB2CF925FAE4F963" box="[1195,1338,1685,1710]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onubensis">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FB2CF925FAE4F963" box="[1195,1338,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. onubensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Guerra- Gacía, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDAFF92FF6CF90AFD06F91F" author="Guerra-Garcia, J. M. &amp; Garcia-Asencio, I. &amp; Sanchez-Moyano, J. E." box="[235,728,1721,1746]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" pagination="333 - 339" refId="ref19798" refString="Guerra-Garcia, J. M., Garcia-Asencio, I. &amp; Sanchez-Moyano, J. E. (2001 a) Parvipalpus onubensis, a new species (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Caprellidea) from the Atlantic coast of Southern Spain. Scientia Marina, 65, 333 - 339. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / scimar. 2001.65 n 4333" type="journal article" year="2001">García-Asencio &amp; Sánchez-Moyano, 2001</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FC9EF909FB40F91F" authority="Guerra-Garcia, 2003" authorityName="Guerra-Garcia" authorityYear="2003" box="[793,1182,1721,1746]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colemani">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FC9EF909FC7FF91F" box="[793,929,1721,1746]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. colemani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDAFF92FC2AF909FB40F91F" author="Guerra-Garcia, J. M." box="[941,1182,1722,1746]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" pagination="171 - 184" refId="ref19327" refString="Guerra-Garcia, J. M. (2003) Two new species of deep-water caprellids (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from northeastern Brazil. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 44, 171 - 184." type="journal article" year="2003">Guerra-García, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The five species are morphologically compared in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDAFF92FE6EF96DFD01F93B" author="Guerra-Garcia, J. M." box="[489,735,1758,1782]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" pagination="171 - 184" refId="ref19327" refString="Guerra-Garcia, J. M. (2003) Two new species of deep-water caprellids (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from northeastern Brazil. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 44, 171 - 184." type="journal article" year="2003">Guerra-García (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B4BFFDAFF92FD6DF96EFBFAF93B" author="McCain, J. C. &amp; Steinberg, J. E." box="[746,1060,1757,1782]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" refId="ref21854" refString="McCain, J. C. &amp; Steinberg, J. E. (1970) Crustaceorum Catalogus: Amphipoda I, Caprellidea I, Family Caprellidae. Dr. W. Junk N. V., Den Haag, 78 pp." type="book" year="1970">McCain &amp; Steinberg (1970)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FB65F96DFAEBF93B" authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1890" box="[1250,1333,1757,1782]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linea">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FB65F96DFAEBF93B" box="[1250,1333,1757,1782]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. linea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be synonym on 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FEAAF8B1FE12F8D7" baseAuthorityName="Chevreux" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[301,460,1793,1818]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capillaceus">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FEAAF8B1FE12F8D7" box="[301,460,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. capillaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FE5BF8B2FD79F8D7" authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1890" box="[476,679,1793,1818]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linea">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FE5BF8B2FD79F8D7" box="[476,679,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">Parvipalpus linea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found so far only in the Mediterranean, 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FB76F8B1FAA8F8D7" authorityName="Guerra-Garcia" authorityYear="2003" box="[1265,1398,1793,1818]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colemani">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FB76F8B1FAA8F8D7" box="[1265,1398,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. colemani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FA00F8B1FED9F8F3" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onubensis">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FA00F8B1FED9F8F3" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. onubensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FEC2F895FE2FF8F3" box="[325,497,1829,1854]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capillaceous">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FEC2F895FE2FF8F3" box="[325,497,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. capillaceous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only in Atlantic waters, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D39FFDAFF92FCE4F895FC1FF8F0" authorityName="A. Carausu" authorityYear="1941" box="[867,961,1830,1853]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Parvipalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="B963EAA8FFDAFF92FCE4F895FC1FF8F0" box="[867,961,1830,1853]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">P. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to present Atlanto-Mediterranean distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
